d 'BOOTUR': module to perform bootstrap unit root tests for single series, multiple series and panels 
d
d	  bootur is a Stata port of the R package bootUR (Smeekes
d and Wilms, 2023). It performs a wide	  range of bootstrap
d augmented Dickey-Fuller (ADF) unit root tests for individual time
d series,    several time series jointly, and panel data. It also
d computes the standard (asymptotic) ADF test	 with MacKinnon
d (1996) p-values, determines the order of integration of each
d series, and provides	  differencing and missing-value/order
d diagnostics.	  Data are supplied as one or more numeric
d variables in wide form (each variable is one time    series, rows
d are time). Series may have different starting and end points
d (unbalanced): the    leading/trailing missing values of each
d series are handled automatically. Internal missing values   
d (gaps) are not allowed.    Six bootstrap schemes are available.
d The moving-block (MBB) and sieve (SB) bootstraps resample    and
d cannot be used with unbalanced panels for the joint tests; the
d wild schemes (BWB, DWB, AWB,	  SWB) can. The union test takes
d the union of rejections over intercept/trend and OLS/QD (GLS)   
d detrending (Harvey, Leybourne and Taylor, 2012; Smeekes and
d Taylor, 2012) and needs no choice of	  deterministic component. 
d See help bootur methods for the underlying algorithm and its
d mapping to	the equations in the references. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: unit root tests
d KW: bootstrap
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260722
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f bootur.ado
f bootur.sthlp
f bootur_example.do
f bootur_methods.sthlp
f ../m/MacroTS.dta
